contentrichtext.text: '''John Austin''' may refer to: * [[John Austin (1613–1669)]], English Catholic writer * [[John Austin (highwayman)]] (died 1783), noted for having been the last person hanged on the famous gallows at Tyburn, London *[[John Austin (Jesuit)]] (1717–1784), Irish Jesuit *[[John Austin (inventor)]] (1752–1830), Scottish inventor of musical equipment * [[John Austin (legal philosopher)]] (1790–1859), legal and political theorist who wrote ''The Province of Jurisprudence Determined'' * [[John Austin (soldier)]] (1801–1833), active in early settlement of Mexican Texas * [[Sir John Austin, 1st Baronet]] (1824–1906), British politician, MP for Osgoldcross, 1886–1906 *[[John Gardiner Austin]], colonial secretary of Hong Kong * [[John Arnold Austin]] (1905–1941), warrant officer in the United States Navy * [[Johnny Austin]] (1910–1983), U.S. musician * [[J. L. Austin]] (John Langshaw Austin, 1911–1960), philosopher of language who wrote ''How to do Things with Words'' * [[John Austin (author)]], British author specializing in WWII propaganda * [[John P. Austin]], American set decorator * [[John Austin (bishop)]] (1939–2007), bishop of Aston * [[John Austin (politician)]] (born 1944), British Labour Party politician, MP since 1992 * [[John Austin (basketball)]] (born 1944), U.S. former professional basketball player *[[John Austin (tennis player)]] (born 1957), former professional tennis player *[[John Austin (artist)]], British railway artist * [[John Alexander Austin]] (1912–1984), Canadian aviator * [[John C. Austin]] (1870–1963), architect and civic leader in Southern California * [[John Beech Austin]] (1917–2012), British aviator in World War II ==See also== *[[John Austen (disambiguation)]] *[[Jack Austin]] (born 1932), Canadian politician *[[Jack Austin (footballer)]] (1910–1983), Australian rules football player {{hndis|Austin, John}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Austin, John}} [[ru:Остин, Джон]]
